  , issueCommentBody =
      "Hi @paramaggarwal,\r\none way of doing this in RethinkDB is to go through JavaScript and use the `r.js()` term.\r\n\r\nHere's an example:\r\n```js\r\nr.expr([\"2012-04-18 05:54:20 +0000\"])\r\n  .map(r.js(\"(function(x) { d = new Date(x); return d.toISOString(); })\"))\r\n  .map(r.ISO8601(r.row))\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that the JavaScript function returns the date string into ISO format, and then we use the `r.ISO8601` term in a second pass to go from there to RethinkDB's native date/time format."
  , issueCommentId = 65115217
